DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       The  mkcluster  utility  creates  a  clustertab  file  and
       installs it as /etc/clustertab on each of the nodes in the
       cluster.  This file is needed to bye in order to configure
       the LLT protocol.  This utility is used  to  automate  the
       creation  of  the  file  and  distribute  it to all of the
       nodes.

OOppttiioonnss
       The following options are  available  with  the  mkcluster
       command:  Specify  the network device to use for LLT traf-
       fic.  Prints the new clustertab to standard output without
       installing it on each node in the cluster.  Enable verbose
       output.

EExxaammppllee
       mkcluster -i /dev/ee16_0 node1 node2 node3 node4

FFiilleess
       /etc/clustertab

RReeffeerreenncceess
NNootteess
       mkcluster requires that each node in the  cluster  provide
       access  for  the  superuser, and it may only be invoked as
       superuser.

       mkcluster assumes that every node in the cluster is  using
       a network interface with the same device name.

